ding sociologist to explore the motivational forces that inspire a sense of group belonging in intimate groups, civic organizations, thought communities, sports and leisure activities, and work. Promoting initiatives that cultivate mindfulness, empathy, altruism, and leadership, Chasing We-ness proposes essential life skills to empower us, reduce social divisions, strengthen the social fabric, and uplift our spirits as global citizens.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 0aAltruism. 0aBelonging (Social psychology). 0aEmpathy. 0aLeadership. 0aMindfulness (Psychology). 4aDISCOUNT-C. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh  aaltruism.  acivic engagement.  acollective consciousness.  acommunity.  acurrent affairs.  aempathy.  agroup belonging.  aleadership.  amindfulness.  apolarization.  apolarized.  asocial capital.  asocial justice.  asociology.  awe-ness.0 cprintz978148754477540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754584040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487545840423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487545840/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles